e: 16px; line-height: 26px; margin: 0 0 1em 0;">With the rise of the creato=
r economy, entrepreneurship, remote work, and web3, more people are pushing=
 for the right to fend for themselves, to set their own course, make their =
own decisions, and bear responsibility for their own actions. I&#8217;m all=
 for it. I work for myself, as a creator, from home, and I am putting more =
and more of my time, net worth, and energy into web3.&nbsp;</p><p style=3D"=
color: #1a1a1a; font-size: 16px; line-height: 26px; margin: 0 0 1em 0;">If =
these trends continue, and if web3 challengers <a href=3D"https://email.mg2=
=2Esubstack.com/c/eJxFkEtuhDAMQE8z2Q3Kd2=
AWWXTTa6B8DESFBCVOEbdvZlBbybJlW9aTnzM=
Ic8qn3lNB8kojnjvoCEdZAREyqQXyGLxmDz4IJZ_Ea-nZoAYSyjhlgM2EVWOuQPZq1-AMhhTfF5=
RyRRY9yUFNg-ulFQw4ezI3scF6YaT0_OnVxTXVB4gONHxDPlMEsuoFcS838XHjny2O4-hiQptyi=
HPnUhvtr_GS7j6UXHcsd1zgt4FcSNCcckafvGdcKSo73hk-eAuDlMIIb5zsFPd1smm7SbrNvCvV=
FjTuqwE2kvUfsK2_FrPB-l60V8dWtxoDniNEY1fwlwW8ZL69jDNEyE2yHw02hYL3sheMCsqvr5s=
m-ZL54D1pZJ_aVfyH_gCdDo2s" rel=3D"" style=3D"color: #1a1a1a; text-decoratio=
n: underline;">disrupt more incumbents</a>, if better APIs and infrastructu=
re make it easier for anyone to build their own products and businesses, if=
 more people work at home, away from bosses, individuals will have a greate=
r ability to shape how the world works than at any point in modern human hi=
story. If you&#8217;re reading this, you&#8217;re likely going to be involv=
ed in that shaping. That&#8217;s an immense amount of freedom, and with it =
comes an immense amount of responsibility.&nbsp;</p><p style=3D"color: #1a1=
a1a; font-size: 16px; line-height: 26px; margin: 0 0 1em 0;">We&#8217;re go=
ing to need to make the transition -- maybe in the next couple years, maybe=
 in the next couple of decades -- from plucky, YOLO-ing underdogs to the pe=
ople responsible for how things work. We&#8217;ll rely on, and get to blame=
, others less than we ever had. We&#8217;ll get to make our own decisions.&=
nbsp;</p><p style=3D"color: #1a1a1a; font-size: 16px; line-height: 26px; ma=
rgin: 0 0 1em 0;">This is one of the reasons I&#8217;m a maximalist minimal=
ist. Fighting over whose blockchain better serves the under 100M people in =
web3 today instead of figuring out a responsible path towards working toget=
her to onboard the next billion users feels silly and inauthentic. And it&#=
8217;s not just blockchain maximalism, but maximalism of all sorts. Wheneve=
r I see maximalism or dogma, I see people who aren&#8217;t ready to handle =
their freedom and make their own meaning.&nbsp;</p><p style=3D"color: #1a1a=
1a; font-size: 16px; line-height: 26px; margin: 0 0 1em 0;">That&#8217;s no=
t to say that we should all act in our own self-interest with disregard for=
 others or that we shouldn&#8217;t join communities. Existentialism is not =
a selfish philosophy. Particularly after the war, Sartre realized that exis=
tentialism needed to cope with togetherness, community, and even morality. =
In <em>Existentialism is a Humanism</em>, he wrote that people should make =
choices as if they&#8217;re making that choice for the whole human race, as=
king, &#8220;Am I really a man who has the right to act in such a manner th=
at humanity regulates itself by what I do?&#8221;</p><p style=3D"color: #1a=
1a1a; font-size: 16px; line-height: 26px; margin: 0 0 1em 0;">Any philosoph=
y for the modern era will need to cope with the idea that our freedom is em=
bedded together, that more than ever, society will be bottoms-up versus top=
-down. If we want to decrease institutional power, we also lower institutio=
nal responsibility. We&#8217;ll need to be responsible for each other. A mo=
dern philosophy will need to confront the fact that we need to create meani=
ng for ourselves, but that life is not meaningless. I hope that nihilism an=
d hedonism don&#8217;t rule the day.&nbsp;</p><p style=3D"color: #1a1a1a; f=
ont-size: 16px; line-height: 26px; margin: 0 0 1em 0;">Last week, there was=
 a meme on twitter about whether DAOs can fire people, kicked off by <a hre=
f=3D"https://email.mg2.substack.com/c/eJxFkEuOwyAMhk9TlhHPhixYjDTqNSICboqaQ=
ETMVLn9OK1GI1l-yNi_-YJHmEs93FZ2ZKcb8djAZXjtCyBCZW2HOqboxFVaZfTAotNRWGNZ2sd7=
BVh9WhzWBmxr05KCx1Tye4JzadjDCSvEYKK4DtMdrNLBij4Io6wX3A5cfnR9iwlyAAc_UI-SgS3=
ugbjtF_V1kTcyfKXzoi6UlaqawtQqlkz5jh7bTonQWkhjjebDVfbcUHVRN1rxLTlLTnIp-CB7em=
O47mTnpY0TWK2VV9EH3RkZ230iAc3XWXZ7m2h3eJ6arLpccCo15Znaz4dfYXk36N8jxbXlhMcI2=
U8LxA8S_JB9QxpnyFCJeBw9Ek8le90rwdUfAmKmT7J0OiPlWGgq_4v-Ag-YjHo" rel=3D"" st=
yle=3D"color: #1a1a1a; text-decoration: underline;">this tweet</a>.&nbsp;&n=
bsp;</p><p style=3D"color: #1a1a1a; font-size: 16px; line-height: 26px; mar=
gin: 0 0 1em 0;">Turns out, people have been fired from DAOs, but I think i=
t highlights the kind of challenges we&#8217;re going to face as things get=
 more decentralized, liquid, and chaotic. New norms, rules, and technology,=
 like something that tracks contributions on-chain, will help, but it will =
be more important than ever for people to think about what it means to take=
 responsibility for themselves.</p><p style=3D"color: #1a1a1a; font-size: 1=
6px; line-height: 26px; margin: 0 0 1em 0;">Existentialism isn&#8217;t perf=
ect. But I think it&#8217;s a good starting point. In the parlance of compo=
sability, it&#8217;s a philosophy lego on top of which a distributed group =
of individual leaders can build. We need modern philosophers -- much better=
 philosophers than me -- to wrestle with modern questions. It would be fool=
ish to be the generation with the most individual agency and the least inte=
ntional thought about what to do with it.&nbsp;</p><p style=3D"color: #1a1a=
1a; font-size: 16px; line-height: 26px; margin: 0 0 1em 0;">No quest is mor=
e optimistic, since it declares that our destiny lies within ourselves.</p>=
